column1: (a) Clearing spread for the bond, in bps, over reference gilt. All successful offers above or at this spread will be allocated at this spread. A dash indicates no successful offers for the bond. Offers at the clearing spread may be scaled.
(c) Percentage allocated to offers at the clearing spread. Offers at the clearing spread are scaled to ensure that the Bank buys no more than the specified maximum in each bond.
(d) Instruments are displayed under their current ticker.
